    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA287-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāppu mikutikkaṇ āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who was unable to bear it during the increase in guarding.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA287">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            vicumpuṟaḻ puricai vempa muṟṟip</l>
<l>            paiṅkaṇ yāṉai vēntupuṟat tiṟutta</l>
<l>            nalleyi luṭaiyō ruṭaiya meṉṉum</l>
<l>            peruntakai maṟavaṉ pōlak koṭuṅkaḻip</l>
<l>            pācaṭai neytaṟ paṉinīrc cērppa </l>
<l>            ṉāma mutalai naṭuṅkupakai yañcāṉ</l>
<l>            kāmam perumaiyiṉ vanta ñāṉṟai</l>
<l>            yarukā tākiya vaṉka ṇeñca</l>
<l>            naḷḷeṉ kaṅkuṟ puḷḷoli kēṭṭoṟun</l>
<l>            tērmaṇit teḷḷicaik kolleṉa </l>
<l>            vūrmaṭi kaṅkulun tuyiṉmaṟan tatuvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>[My] strong heart, that was not afraid</l>
<l rend="indent">at the time he came, for desire [is] great,</l>
<l rend="indent2">without fear of the shivering<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">naṭuṅku pakai</term>: here actually the Tamil is imprecise (as is poetic licence); in fact the enmity should be one that makes shiver.</note> enmity of the fear[-ful] crocodile,</l>
<l rend="indent">– the man from the coast of chilly waters with green-leaved</l>
<l rend="indent">blue waterlilies</l>
<l rend="indent3">in curved backwaters, like an excellent warrior<note place="foot">Here <term xml:lang="ta">maṟavaṉ</term> clearly refers to a warrior (be it inside or outside the fortification) and not to a highway robber. The formulaic epithet <term xml:lang="ta">perum-takai</term>, literally "of great fitness", seems weakened to a mere assertion of positive qualities.</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">who says “we have those that have a good fortress,</l>
<l rend="indent4">where a king with green-eyed elephants tarried outside,</l>
<l rend="indent4">the fortifications up to the sky furiously<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vempa</term> in an adverbial sense and meaning "quickly"?</note> completed,” –</l>
<l>whenever it hears the birds’ sound deep at night,</l>
<l>[asking]</l>
<l rend="indent4">“[is it] the clear sound of [his] chariot’s bells?”,</l>
<l>all [this] night, when the village droops, it has forgotten sleep.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
